FBIS3-7119 "dreas057_l_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-057 Document Type:Daily Report 24 Mar 1994 Philippines Senators Comment on Korean Peninsula Issue BK2403072294 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 0500 GMT 24 Mar 94 BK2403072294 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network Language: Tagalog Article Type:BFN [Text] The Philippines will be forced to send troops to North Korea if war breaks out there. This was revealed by Senator Blas Ople, chairman of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee. He emphasized that the country, being a member of the United Nations, should lead in sending troops to North Korea. Ople also asked the government to take appropriate action to safeguard the estimated 40,000 Filipinos in Korea [as heard]. Meanwhile, Senator Rodolfo Biazon, former Armed Forces of the Philippines chief, hopes the current situation in Korea will not result in war.
